instruction:
Classic switch matches exact values. Modern `switch` expression (Java 14+) uses `->` arrows and returns values — no `break` needed:

```java
String result = switch (day) {
    case "MON", "TUE" -> "Weekday";
    case "SAT", "SUN" -> "Weekend";
    default -> "Unknown";
};
```

Run both versions and see the difference.

