            default -> "No access";
        };
        System.out.println(access);
    }
}

instruction:
Classic `instanceof` checks type. Java 16+ adds pattern matching — it assigns AND checks in one step:

```java
// Old:
if (obj instanceof String) {
    String s = (String) obj;
}

// New (pattern matching):
if (obj instanceof String s) {
    // s is already a String here!
}
```

